It is challenging to provide an accurate summary of what most women in East Timor think of abortion as opinions on this topic can vary among individuals. However, it is important to note that East Timor is a predominantly Catholic country, and Catholic teachings generally oppose abortion. The Catholic Church considers abortion as morally wrong and a violation of the sanctity of life. As a result, many women in East Timor may adhere to these religious beliefs and hold negative views towards abortion.

However, it is also worth mentioning that East Timor has a complex social and cultural landscape, and there may be diverse perspectives on abortion within the country. Some women might support the right to choose and advocate for access to safe and legal abortion services, considering factors such as women's reproductive rights, health, and socio-economic circumstances.

To gain a more comprehensive understanding of the opinions of women in East Timor regarding abortion, it would be necessary to conduct surveys, interviews, or studies specifically focused on this topic within the country.
